// Orchicon PolicyService (docs/07_API_Specification.md §3.5).
//
// Policy CRUD + versioning lifecycle (publish/supersede) + dry-run
// evaluation + decision explanation. Tier 1 (decision-point) policy is
// the v0.1 baseline, always-on, Rego-only. All mutations write through
// the transactional outbox (docs/09 §6). A published Policy version is
// immutable; changes create a new version (docs/02 §2.5).
//
// Policies are evaluated in order of narrowest scope first; first
// definitive decision wins (docs/02 §2.5). EvaluatePolicy runs a dry-run
// against a decision point + input without persisting a decision;
// ExplainDecision returns the Rego evaluation trace for a past
// `policy.evaluated` event by decision_id or trace_id.

